     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The northern corridor's major hub, with genuine owner-occupier streets behind the retail facade.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Chermside sits approximately nine kilometres north of the Brisbane CBD, centred on the Gympie Road corridor that connects the northern suburbs to the city. The suburb is anchored by Westfield Chermside, one of Queensland's largest shopping centres, and by Prince Charles Hospital, a major public health facility that draws healthcare workers from across the northern corridor. Beyond the retail and hospital precinct, Chermside has a substantial residential character that is often underestimated by buyers who know the suburb only by its commercial face.
    </p>
